Kahal B’raira (KB), is Greater Boston’s vibrant and growing congregation for Humanistic Judaism. We have a diverse membership who seek an engaging, non-theistic way to connect themselves and their children with Jewish history, traditions, literature, and music. Members believe in the human capacity to create a better world. 

The Managing Director supervises every aspect of the congregation’s functioning. This includes: 
• Working closely with the president and executive committee; 
• Supervising core staff (education director, music director, and facilities personnel); 
• Recruiting and helping to train volunteers 
• Maintaining open lines of communication with members through a monthly bulletin, listserv notices, personal contact, and the website; 
• Working with our Treasurer and an outside accountant to manage the congregation’s finances (including performing a variety of administrative tasks);
• Assisting with programming, outreach, and fundraising;

Candidates who prefer a part-time position are encouraged to apply; as a small congregation KB both values and offers flexibility.

Please visit https://kahalbraira.org/ to learn more about our unique congregation. Go to https://shj.org/ for more information about Humanistic Judaism. Then apply by sending a cover letter and resume.

