RISE is a division of JRI Health that provides services to people in the Metro West area, Framingham. Our services include free confidential HIV counseling, testing and referrals, STI and Hepatitis testing, HIV Case Management, Housing  Search & Advocacy, Peer Support Services, LGBT services,  Overdose Prevention and Education, Needle Exchange, community education programs on HIV, STIs, viral Hepatitis, harm reduction, and LGBTQ cultural competency. 

RESPONSIBILITIES

The Substance Use Specialist is a full-time staff position and reports directly to the Director of Quality Assurance.

•Provide substance use assessment, develop individualized service plan, treatment, and referral services to individuals enrolled in JRI programs;
•Counsel clients or participants, individually or in group sessions, to assist in addressing substance use behaviors and their impact using a harm reduction approach;  
•Provide training to staff regarding substance use, overdose prevention, harm reduction and related topics;
•Assist in the development of JRI policies, procedures and program development regarding substance use;
•Provide follow up to JRI programs in response to overdoses and narcan administration;
•Provide clinical supervision to staff administering naloxone and respond to unintentional overdoses;
•Compile resources regarding to substance use treatment;
•Participate in JRI’s Substance Use Workgroup to develop agency-wide strategies for responding to substance use. 

QUALIFICATIONS

•Minimum Master’s Degree or above in the mental health field, must be licensed or license eligible (LICSW, LMHC, LCSW or LMFT;
•Understanding of and experience applying harm reduction principles as well as other evidence-based practices such as motivational interviewing;
•Familiarity with the substance use treatment system and ability to navigate it.

This position includes medical, dental, vision, 401K with company match, company sponsored pension plan, employer paid life insurance, generous personal time off package, flexible spending accounts for dependent care, tuition reimbursement, long and short term disability, opportunities for continued education/training and much more!

JRI is an equal opportunity employer and is strongly committed to building and maintaining a diverse community.  Persons from diverse backgrounds including women, communities of color, the LGBTQ community and people with disabilities are encouraged to apply.
